Deep within the darkened, unknown barrier cast a dreary, sweetened scent from off the vale. It was a calming, soothing aroma of enlightenment that hugged her nostrils with the soft hands of a child- a silicone smell that reminded the young artist of newly made toys gifted upon the upcoming of holidays; picked right off the workshop counter. In some innate sense, she could feel the softness of the covers she wrapped herself into only minutes before lining silk in between her fingers. The unknown nostalgia, a wild concoction of odd sadness and happiness all at once, felt unusual in such a opaque environment. The floor was of unknown range, and a choir of whispers resided upon her head, feeling pupils forming upon her back that blended in with the darkness, and yet, she wasn't afraid. Perhaps the brunette had been here before?
As she mindlessly observed her tiny hands, scintillas of chakra immersed like morning stars, swirling around her fingertips and glittering into the air before her. Her chin lifted, multi-shaded orbs sparkling hues of the newfound beauty, silently watching it float up and away form her grasp.
"There are many months ahead of you, my friend."
The young artist jumped on the newfound voice, soaked with the evidence of familiar a young boy in earshot. The scintillas grouped together like migrating monarches, butterfly wings conjoined to create a wisp of faint fire; a flaming amber spirit emerging from the ashes of previous life. Innocent forest eyes flared the colors of summer leaves among the atmosphere. The hair was curled and the face was rounded, signifying a fairly early time of death. A faint breath emerged from her lips.
"Kuto!"
A memory recalled a flaming spirit among the remains of a torn down circus- a talented young boy with several lashes imprinted with an ugly salmon on a fragile spine; constant force from unfriendly tamers. Even though his talents were forced, he sparked a brilliant light from deep within his core on the stagelight's last gleam.
"...G-Greetings! Golly, it's been awhile since I've seen you. How are... Things holding up...?"
